# Concurrent appends to the brain ledger merge cleanly: `union` keeps BOTH sides' new
# tail lines instead of conflicting. This is what lets multiple sessions / proposals
# add lessons without clobbering each other (council 2026-06-16). It resolves only the
# textual tail-append case — semantic merges (consolidation, supersession) stay a
# serialized maintainer pass, never concurrent.
skills/cogito-protocol/LESSONS.md merge=union
skills/cogito-protocol/LESSONS-ARCHIVE.md merge=union
